---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="FAQ" description="Frequently asked questions about the Los Angeles Bicycle Advisory Committee.">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">What is LABAC?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">LABAC is the Los Angeles Bicycle Advisory Committee, an advisory body to the City of Los Angeles on bicycle transportation. It was established in 1975.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">When does the committee meet?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">LABAC meets on the first Tuesday of every even-numbered month (February, April, June, August, October, December) at 7:00 PM.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Where are meetings held?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">Meetings are held at Los Angeles City Hall, 200 N Spring St, Los Angeles, CA 90012.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">How are members appointed?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">Members are appointed by City Council members, with each council district represented on the committee.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Can I attend a meeting?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">Yes! All LABAC meetings are open to the public. You can attend in person and provide public comment during the designated portion of the meeting.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-2">How do I request a bike lane or report an issue?</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted">You can submit a request to LADOT or bring the issue to LABAC during public comment at a meeting. See our <a href="/resources" class="text-primary hover:underline">Resources</a> page for more options.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
